# GUI Module Conventions

**"Module" here means a domain module (bounded context in DDD)**—a topic or area the user can work on, such as Organizations, Objectives, Initiatives, Key Results, Focus Areas. This is not about Nuxt modules or technical modules.

Apply these conventions consistently to every domain module in the GUI.

## Icons

- Each module has a **consistently used icon** that appears everywhere there is a link to that module.

## Module Menu

- All modules as defined in these conventions are shown in a **menu**.
- The menu can **collapse** and expand.
- A **button to open** the menu is placed in the **top bar** of the application (like a drawer).
- When opened, the drawer reveals the full list of modules for navigation.

## Top Bar and Module Name

- Each GUI module presents its **module name** in the top bar, next to the application's name.
- The module name reflects the current context (e.g., "Organizations", "Objectives", "Key Results").

## Breadcrumbs

- Each page starts with a component that displays a **clickable breadcrumb**.
- The **root node** of the breadcrumb is always **Welcome**.
- **Path retention**: When the user navigates by clicking through from one module (or record) to another—for example, from an Organization to its Objectives, or from a referenced value to its detail page—the breadcrumb **retains the path** and shows the full trail (e.g., `Welcome > Organizations > Acme Corp > Objectives`).
- **Path reset**: When the user navigates via the **menu** or the **welcome page**, the breadcrumb is **reset**. Any prior navigations are lost, and the path becomes `Welcome > [modulename]` (e.g., `Welcome > Organizations`).
- Breadcrumb segments are clickable and navigate back to that point in the path.

## Unsaved Changes on Navigation

- Before any navigation between modules occurs, the application **checks if there are unsaved changes** in any input forms.
- If unsaved changes exist:
  - **Prompt the user** with a choice:
    - Navigate and abandon the changes.
    - Stay on the current page and keep editing.
  - Do not navigate until the user explicitly chooses one option.
- This applies to all navigation triggers: menu clicks, links, back/forward, and any other way the user might leave the current module.

## Quick-Add Feature

- Each module has a **quick-add** feature that opens an overlay over the current page.
- Quick-add is accessible from every location in the application.
- **Invocation**: A `+` icon in the top-right bar. When clicked, a small overlay appears with:
  - A list of modules to choose from.
  - Each option shows the module icon and the module name.
  - Selecting an option opens that module's quick-add overlay.
- **Content parity**: The quick-add overlay must show the **same form and fields** as the module's normal add flow (e.g. the "Create New" page). It is the same functionality, presented in an overlay instead of a full page.
- **Actions**: The quick-add overlay has:
  - **Cancel**: Closes the overlay without saving.
  - **Save**: Persists the new record and closes the overlay.

## Internationalization

- Every piece of text in the application is stored in a **translation file per module** (in the `i18n` folder).

## Relations Between Modules

- Relations between modules are managed by **searchable dropdowns** that let users search records within the related module.
- When a reference is shown in a dropdown, display records according to the **module template** (see below).

## Form Validation

- When a form is invalid:
  - Invalid fields are **immediately shown** (inline validation).
  - The **Save button is greyed out** until the form is valid.

## Module Overview References (Cards)

- References to a module's overview page use **cards** that display:
  - The module icon.
  - The module title.
  - A short description.

## Delete with References

- Users can delete records.
- When a record has references from other modules:
  - **Inform the user** which records will be affected.
  - Show the **referencing module** and a **filter icon**.
  - When the user clicks the filter icon:
    - Navigate to the referencing module's overview page.
    - Apply a filter to show only the affected records.
    - **Cancel** the delete operation.

## Module Templates

- Each module has a **template** that defines how a record is represented elsewhere.
- The template specifies which fields are shown when the record is referenced.
- Dropdowns and references display records according to this template.

## Detail Page Headers

- When a detail page displays a single record, the **page header** (e.g. the main title) must be formatted **congruently** with how the record is shown elsewhere.
- Use the **module template** to format the header—the same format used for breadcrumbs, dropdowns, and references.
- Avoid showing only the primary field (e.g. name or title) in the header. Use the full template format so the visitor sees a consistent representation of the record across the application.

## Admin Card

Each module's overview page has an **admin card** above the data table. The admin card contains:

### Data Model Icon

- An icon representing the data model. When clicked, a **dialog** asks which format the user wants for the data model of this module:
  - **JSON** — schema or structure as JSON.
  - **CREATE TABLE statements** — SQL DDL for the tables.
  - **Visual diagram** — navigates to a page that shows the data model visually and hierarchically (tables, structures, and how they interrelate).

### Export Data Icon

- An icon to export the current set of data shown in the table below. When clicked, a **dialog** asks:
  - **CSV** — export the visible rows as CSV.
  - **INSERT statements** — export as SQL INSERT statements, with a **checkbox** to optionally include CREATE TABLE statements in the output.

## Overview Mode

- Opening a module always enters **overview mode** first.
- This table form also applies **within detail pages** where the user manages records within the parent record (e.g. positions within organization structures, key results within an objective).
- Overview mode uses a **v-data-table** implemented as a **server-side table** (see [Vuetify server-side tables](https://vuetifyjs.com/en/components/data-tables/basics/#server-side-tables)), with:
  - **Header row**: Describes the shown information in each column. Use the header row for the adding functionality of the module (e.g. add button or link in the header).
  - **Pagination**: Always show pagination controls.
  - **Logical sorting**: Support sortable columns with server-side sorting.
  - **Filtering**: Support filtering with server-side filtering.
  - **Left column**: Fixed checkbox for bulk-mode, then icon to start edit mode.
  - **Right column**: Fixed icon to start delete (always followed by the delete confirmation dialogue).
  - **Middle columns**: Relevant record data; these columns may scroll horizontally.
  - Outer icons and checkboxes remain **stationary**; only the middle content scrolls.
  - **Icon, checkbox, and color-indicator columns**: All columns that contain only an icon, checkbox, or color indicator use the **same small fixed width**, just large enough to accommodate their contents.

### Bulk-Mode Checkbox

- Next to the edit icon, each row has a **checkbox for bulk-mode**.
- When the module has a **color value** for records, display the color in a **circle next to the checkbox**.
- **Header row checkbox** behavior:
  - When **none selected**: Checking selects all visible rows (respecting current page/filter).
  - When **some selected**: The header checkbox shows as checked (or indeterminate). Checking it **deselects all** first.
  - When **all selected**: Checking deselects all.

### Bulk Actions

When one or more rows are selected in bulk-mode, the following actions are available:

- **Export all selected records** — Starts the export modal, scoped to the selected records.
- **Delete all selected records** — Starts the delete modal, adjusted for bulk-mode (e.g. shows count of selected records, confirms deletion of all selected).

## Referenced Values in Overview

- When a referenced value is shown in the overview:
  - Format it according to the **module template**.
  - Show an **icon next to it**; clicking it navigates to the detail page of that record.
